      <Content>&lt;p&gt;Recently I had to dig into the &lt;a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/default.asp?url=/library/en-us/multimed/htm/_win32_audio_mixers.asp"&gt;Windows&amp;nbsp;Audio Mixer APIs&lt;/a&gt; for the next release of &lt;a href="http://www.it99.org/axl/PermaLink,guid,f41dbb1e-e1d2-4a9f-8562-cf9126622c5a.aspx"&gt;Tranquilizer&lt;/a&gt;. It has taken time to understand the&amp;nbsp;architecture of these APIs. A&amp;nbsp;handy utility that comes into play when exploring the mixers and their&amp;nbsp;features that are available on a certain system is the &lt;a href="http://media.virtuosi.fi/users/pdonner/mixerbrowser/"&gt;Mixer Browser&lt;/a&gt; written by &lt;a href="http://media.virtuosi.fi/users/pdonner/"&gt;Philip Donner&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;a title="Mixer Browser" href="http://www.it99.org/axl/content/binary/Mixer%20Browser%20Screenshot.png" rel="lightbox"&gt;&lt;img alt="Mixer Browser Screenshot" src="http://www.it99.org/axl/content/binary/Mixer%20Browser%20Screenshot%20small.png" border="0"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img title="Download" class="download" style="margin-right: 4px;" alt="Download" src="http://www.it99.org/axl/content/binary/Download.gif"&gt;I've mirrored the &lt;a href="http://www.it99.org/axl/download/MixerBrowser-1.4.zip"&gt;Mixer Browser 1.4 executable&lt;/a&gt; in case the page disappears.&lt;/p&gt;
